# Planning

## Project Planning Documentation

### Sprint Planning
**Goal:** Build a simple PyQt5 desktop application with a main window containing two vertically stacked sections. Each section will have a label and a read-only text display area.

**Sprint 1:**
- Set up project structure and dependencies
- Implement main window with two sections
- Add labels and read-only text displays
- Test basic UI functionality

### Feature Planning
**Features:**
1. Main window using PyQt5
2. Two sections displayed vertically
3. Each section contains:
   - A label
   - A read-only text display area
4. Clean, simple UI layout
5. Modern visual style: use PyQt5 stylesheets, spacing, and fonts for a contemporary look

### Architecture Planning
**Architecture:**
- Use PyQt5 for GUI
- Organize code into modules: main app, UI components
- Follow PEP8 and project coding standards
- Keep code modular and maintainable

### Tasks
**Task Breakdown:**
1. Project setup and install PyQt5
2. Create main window class
3. Implement vertical layout with two sections
4. Add label and read-only text display to each section
5. Apply modern styles (fonts, spacing, colors)
6. Test UI functionality
7. Refactor and finalize documentation

### Resource Planning
**Resources:**
- Python 3.x
- PyQt5
- Developer: 1 (you)
- IDE: VS Code
